author: stefan2
msg: Make XDelta operation simpler, faster and somewhat more effective:
* for lookup, use blocks with exactly MATCH_BLOCKSIZE only
(might miss a sub-length match at the end of *both* windows
-> rare and less than 60 bytes worst-case overhead per window)
* make blocks hash table support multiple blocks with the same
Adler32 sum but different content (little actual overhead because
the content needs to be compared anyways; very useful for large
values of SVN_DELTA_WINDOW_SIZE)
* subversion/libsvn_delta/xdelta.c
(adler32.len, adler32_in, adler32_out): unused -> remove
(adler32_replace): adapt doc string
(init_adler32, init_blocks_table): use fixed block size
(blocks, add_block, find_block): support multiple entries per adler32 value
(match_length): fix commentary
(find_match): use fixed block size; reduce signature
(compute_delta): use fixed block size only; reduce number of local variables
